The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 4: The government has cleared 29 foreign direct investment proposals that will inject Rs 616.08 crore into the country. More than half of the FDI will be brought in by Accors Singapore arm. The company plans to invest Rs 365.78 crore in an Indian company to construct and manage low-budget hotels. The proposal by cargo-handling company ABG Bulk Handling was also approved by the Foreign Investment Promotion Board.                             
	 New Delhi, March 4: Global rating agency Moodys has downgraded its credit rating on Tata Steel because of the firms deteriorating operating performance and warned of further downgrade in the wake of continuing demand and pricing slump in the industry. Tata Steel rating has been downgraded to Ba2 from Ba1, Moodys Investors Service said.                             
	 Calcutta, March 4: Bhushan Energy has moved the Company Law Board against the promoters of Orissa Sponge. In its petition filed on March 2, Bhushan Energy alleged that the promoters had used the companys funds to buy shares of the company.                                                                                                                           
